[
  {
    "text": "When I heard those bars",
    "start": 12.76,
    "duration": 3.576
  },
  {
    "text": "slam hard,",
    "start": 16.36,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "I knew it was for real.",
    "start": 20.119,
    "duration": 1.721
  },
  {
    "text": "I feel confused.",
    "start": 23.52,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "I feel betrayed.",
    "start": 26.48,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "I feel overwhelmed.",
    "start": 29.88,
    "duration": 2.8
  },
  {
    "text": "I feel silenced.",
    "start": 33.76,
    "duration": 2.72
  },
  {
    "text": "What just happened?",
    "start": 37.76,
    "duration": 1.32
  },
  {
    "text": "How could they send me here?",
    "start": 40.68,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "I don't belong here.",
    "start": 44.04,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "How could they make such a huge mistake",
    "start": 47.36,
    "duration": 3.896
  },
  {
    "text": "without any repercussions\nwhatsoever to their actions?",
    "start": 51.28,
    "duration": 4.4
  },
  {
    "text": "I see large groups of women",
    "start": 57.08,
    "duration": 3.416
  },
  {
    "text": "in tattered uniforms",
    "start": 60.52,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "surrounded by huge walls and gates,",
    "start": 62.88,
    "duration": 4.536
  },
  {
    "text": "enclosed by iron barbed wires,",
    "start": 67.44,
    "duration": 3.296
  },
  {
    "text": "and I get hit by an awful stench,",
    "start": 70.76,
    "duration": 3.32
  },
  {
    "text": "and I ask myself,",
    "start": 74.88,
    "duration": 1.52
  },
  {
    "text": "how did I move",
    "start": 77.519,
    "duration": 1.801
  },
  {
    "text": "from working in the respected\nfinancial banking sector,",
    "start": 80.32,
    "duration": 4.84
  },
  {
    "text": "having worked so hard in school,",
    "start": 86.12,
    "duration": 3.0
  },
  {
    "text": "to now being locked up",
    "start": 90.0,
    "duration": 2.576
  },
  {
    "text": "in the largest correctional facility",
    "start": 92.6,
    "duration": 3.216
  },
  {
    "text": "for women in Kenya?",
    "start": 95.84,
    "duration": 2.08
  },
  {
    "text": "My first night",
    "start": 99.52,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "at Langata Women Maximum Security Prison",
    "start": 101.68,
    "duration": 4.136
  },
  {
    "text": "was the toughest.",
    "start": 105.84,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "In January of 2009,",
    "start": 108.4,
    "duration": 3.056
  },
  {
    "text": "I was informed that I had handled\na fraudulent transaction unknowingly",
    "start": 111.48,
    "duration": 4.656
  },
  {
    "text": "at the bank where I worked.",
    "start": 116.16,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "I was shocked, scared and terrified.",
    "start": 118.68,
    "duration": 4.616
  },
  {
    "text": "I would lose a career\nthat I loved passionately.",
    "start": 123.32,
    "duration": 3.96
  },
  {
    "text": "But that was not the worst.",
    "start": 129.32,
    "duration": 3.056
  },
  {
    "text": "It got even worse\nthan I could have ever imagined.",
    "start": 132.4,
    "duration": 4.12
  },
  {
    "text": "I got arrested,",
    "start": 137.92,
    "duration": 1.6
  },
  {
    "text": "maliciously charged",
    "start": 140.44,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "and prosecuted.",
    "start": 142.6,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "The absurdity of it all\nwas the arresting officer",
    "start": 146.44,
    "duration": 4.576
  },
  {
    "text": "asking me to pay him 10,000 US dollars",
    "start": 151.04,
    "duration": 5.136
  },
  {
    "text": "and the case would disappear.",
    "start": 156.2,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "I refused.",
    "start": 159.84,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "Two and a half years on,",
    "start": 162.56,
    "duration": 2.736
  },
  {
    "text": "in and out of courts,",
    "start": 165.32,
    "duration": 1.736
  },
  {
    "text": "fighting to prove my innocence.",
    "start": 167.08,
    "duration": 3.456
  },
  {
    "text": "It was all over the media,",
    "start": 170.56,
    "duration": 2.976
  },
  {
    "text": "in the newspapers, TV, radio.",
    "start": 173.56,
    "duration": 4.136
  },
  {
    "text": "They came to me again.",
    "start": 177.72,
    "duration": 1.56
  },
  {
    "text": "This time around, said to me,",
    "start": 180.12,
    "duration": 3.456
  },
  {
    "text": "\"If you give us 50,000 US dollars,",
    "start": 183.6,
    "duration": 4.48
  },
  {
    "text": "the judgement will be in your favor,\"",
    "start": 189.08,
    "duration": 3.2
  },
  {
    "text": "irrespective of the fact\nthat there was no evidence whatsoever",
    "start": 193.48,
    "duration": 4.08
  },
  {
    "text": "that I had any wrongdoing",
    "start": 198.48,
    "duration": 2.216
  },
  {
    "text": "on the charges that I was up against.",
    "start": 200.72,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "I remember the events",
    "start": 205.28,
    "duration": 2.456
  },
  {
    "text": "of my conviction",
    "start": 207.76,
    "duration": 1.856
  },
  {
    "text": "six years ago",
    "start": 209.64,
    "duration": 2.576
  },
  {
    "text": "as if it were yesterday.",
    "start": 212.24,
    "duration": 1.68
  },
  {
    "text": "The cold, hard face of the judge",
    "start": 215.32,
    "duration": 3.576
  },
  {
    "text": "as she pronounced my sentence",
    "start": 218.92,
    "duration": 2.776
  },
  {
    "text": "on a cold Thursday morning",
    "start": 221.72,
    "duration": 2.16
  },
  {
    "text": "for a crime that I hadn't committed.",
    "start": 225.08,
    "duration": 2.96
  },
  {
    "text": "I remember holding",
    "start": 229.16,
    "duration": 1.976
  },
  {
    "text": "my three-month-old beautiful daughter",
    "start": 231.16,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "whom I had just named Oma,",
    "start": 235.08,
    "duration": 2.32
  },
  {
    "text": "which in my dialect\nmeans \"truth and justice,\"",
    "start": 238.28,
    "duration": 4.456
  },
  {
    "text": "as that was what I had longed so much for",
    "start": 242.76,
    "duration": 4.856
  },
  {
    "text": "all this time.",
    "start": 247.64,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "I dressed her in her\nfavorite purple dress,",
    "start": 249.96,
    "duration": 3.616
  },
  {
    "text": "and here she was, about to accompany me",
    "start": 253.6,
    "duration": 3.44
  },
  {
    "text": "to serve this one-year sentence",
    "start": 257.84,
    "duration": 2.736
  },
  {
    "text": "behind bars.",
    "start": 260.6,
    "duration": 1.36
  },
  {
    "text": "The guards did not seem\nsensitive to the trauma",
    "start": 264.28,
    "duration": 3.736
  },
  {
    "text": "that this experience was causing me.",
    "start": 268.04,
    "duration": 2.96
  },
  {
    "text": "My dignity and humanity disappeared",
    "start": 272.44,
    "duration": 3.96
  },
  {
    "text": "with the admission process.",
    "start": 277.32,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "It involved me being\nsearched for contrabands,",
    "start": 281.84,
    "duration": 3.16
  },
  {
    "text": "changed from my ordinary clothes",
    "start": 286.68,
    "duration": 3.296
  },
  {
    "text": "to the prison uniform,",
    "start": 290.0,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "forced to squat on the ground,",
    "start": 291.92,
    "duration": 2.68
  },
  {
    "text": "a posture that I soon came to learn",
    "start": 295.8,
    "duration": 2.48
  },
  {
    "text": "would form the routine",
    "start": 299.08,
    "duration": 2.856
  },
  {
    "text": "of the thousands of searches,",
    "start": 301.96,
    "duration": 2.48
  },
  {
    "text": "number counts,",
    "start": 305.2,
    "duration": 1.496
  },
  {
    "text": "that lay ahead of me.",
    "start": 306.72,
    "duration": 1.48
  },
  {
    "text": "The women told me,",
    "start": 311.0,
    "duration": 1.48
  },
  {
    "text": "\"You'll adjust to this place.",
    "start": 313.36,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "You'll fit right in.\"",
    "start": 316.2,
    "duration": 1.68
  },
  {
    "text": "I was no longer referred to\nas Teresa Njoroge.",
    "start": 319.28,
    "duration": 4.056
  },
  {
    "text": "The number 415/11 was my new identity,",
    "start": 323.36,
    "duration": 4.736
  },
  {
    "text": "and I soon learned that was\nthe case with the other women",
    "start": 328.12,
    "duration": 3.816
  },
  {
    "text": "who we were sharing this space with.",
    "start": 331.96,
    "duration": 2.32
  },
  {
    "text": "And adjust I did to life on the inside:",
    "start": 336.04,
    "duration": 3.68
  },
  {
    "text": "the prison food,",
    "start": 340.68,
    "duration": 1.48
  },
  {
    "text": "the prison language,",
    "start": 343.16,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "the prison life.",
    "start": 345.92,
    "duration": 1.976
  },
  {
    "text": "Prison is certainly no fairytale world.",
    "start": 347.92,
    "duration": 4.76
  },
  {
    "text": "What I didn't see come my way",
    "start": 354.72,
    "duration": 2.616
  },
  {
    "text": "was the women and children",
    "start": 357.36,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "whom we served time and shared space with,",
    "start": 361.84,
    "duration": 4.08
  },
  {
    "text": "women who had been imprisoned",
    "start": 367.56,
    "duration": 3.896
  },
  {
    "text": "for crimes of the system,",
    "start": 371.48,
    "duration": 3.056
  },
  {
    "text": "the corruption that requires a fall guy,",
    "start": 374.56,
    "duration": 4.76
  },
  {
    "text": "a scapegoat,",
    "start": 380.24,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "so that the person who is responsible",
    "start": 382.16,
    "duration": 2.856
  },
  {
    "text": "could go free,",
    "start": 385.04,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "a broken system that routinely\nvilifies the vulnerable,",
    "start": 387.6,
    "duration": 6.656
  },
  {
    "text": "the poorest amongst us,",
    "start": 394.28,
    "duration": 2.296
  },
  {
    "text": "people who cannot afford to pay bail",
    "start": 396.6,
    "duration": 3.096
  },
  {
    "text": "or bribes.",
    "start": 399.72,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "And so we moved on.",
    "start": 403.56,
    "duration": 1.32
  },
  {
    "text": "As I listened to story after story",
    "start": 406.76,
    "duration": 2.936
  },
  {
    "text": "of these close to 700 women",
    "start": 409.72,
    "duration": 3.216
  },
  {
    "text": "during that one year in prison,",
    "start": 412.96,
    "duration": 2.96
  },
  {
    "text": "I soon realized that crime",
    "start": 417.36,
    "duration": 3.896
  },
  {
    "text": "was not what had brought\nthese women to prison,",
    "start": 421.28,
    "duration": 4.16
  },
  {
    "text": "most of them,",
    "start": 426.48,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "far from it.",
    "start": 428.48,
    "duration": 1.6
  },
  {
    "text": "It had started with the education system,",
    "start": 431.0,
    "duration": 4.24
  },
  {
    "text": "whose supply and quality\nis not equal for all;",
    "start": 436.8,
    "duration": 4.36
  },
  {
    "text": "lack of economic opportunities",
    "start": 442.28,
    "duration": 2.96
  },
  {
    "text": "that pushes these women\nto petty survival crimes;",
    "start": 446.24,
    "duration": 4.856
  },
  {
    "text": "the health system,",
    "start": 451.12,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "social justice system,",
    "start": 453.28,
    "duration": 2.216
  },
  {
    "text": "the criminal justice system.",
    "start": 455.52,
    "duration": 2.416
  },
  {
    "text": "If any of these women,",
    "start": 457.96,
    "duration": 2.416
  },
  {
    "text": "who were mostly from poor backgrounds,",
    "start": 460.4,
    "duration": 2.856
  },
  {
    "text": "fall through the cracks",
    "start": 463.28,
    "duration": 2.696
  },
  {
    "text": "in the already broken system,",
    "start": 466.0,
    "duration": 3.056
  },
  {
    "text": "the bottom of that chasm is a prison,",
    "start": 469.08,
    "duration": 3.776
  },
  {
    "text": "period.",
    "start": 472.88,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "By the time I completed\nmy one-year sentence",
    "start": 476.44,
    "duration": 3.296
  },
  {
    "text": "at Langata Women Maximum Prison,",
    "start": 479.76,
    "duration": 2.36
  },
  {
    "text": "I had a burning conviction",
    "start": 483.0,
    "duration": 2.56
  },
  {
    "text": "to be part of the transformation",
    "start": 486.96,
    "duration": 3.896
  },
  {
    "text": "to resolve the injustices",
    "start": 490.88,
    "duration": 2.536
  },
  {
    "text": "that I had witnessed",
    "start": 493.44,
    "duration": 1.696
  },
  {
    "text": "of women and girls",
    "start": 495.16,
    "duration": 1.736
  },
  {
    "text": "who were caught up in a revolving door",
    "start": 496.92,
    "duration": 2.776
  },
  {
    "text": "of a life in and out of prison",
    "start": 499.72,
    "duration": 2.536
  },
  {
    "text": "due to poverty.",
    "start": 502.28,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "After my release,",
    "start": 505.6,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "I set up Clean Start.",
    "start": 507.52,
    "duration": 1.84
  },
  {
    "text": "Clean Start is a social enterprise",
    "start": 510.32,
    "duration": 3.496
  },
  {
    "text": "that seeks to give these women and girls",
    "start": 513.84,
    "duration": 2.976
  },
  {
    "text": "a second chance.",
    "start": 516.84,
    "duration": 1.44
  },
  {
    "text": "What we do is we build bridges for them.",
    "start": 519.2,
    "duration": 3.696
  },
  {
    "text": "We go into the prisons, train them,",
    "start": 522.92,
    "duration": 2.776
  },
  {
    "text": "give them skills, tools and support",
    "start": 525.72,
    "duration": 3.055
  },
  {
    "text": "to enable them to be able\nto change their mindsets,",
    "start": 528.799,
    "duration": 3.417
  },
  {
    "text": "their behaviors and their attitudes.",
    "start": 532.24,
    "duration": 2.319
  },
  {
    "text": "We also build bridges into the prisons",
    "start": 535.4,
    "duration": 4.416
  },
  {
    "text": "from the corporate sector --",
    "start": 539.84,
    "duration": 1.976
  },
  {
    "text": "individuals, organizations",
    "start": 541.84,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "that will partner with Clean Start",
    "start": 544.0,
    "duration": 1.976
  },
  {
    "text": "to enable us to provide employment,",
    "start": 546.0,
    "duration": 2.416
  },
  {
    "text": "places to call home,",
    "start": 548.44,
    "duration": 2.056
  },
  {
    "text": "jobs, vocational training,",
    "start": 550.52,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "for these women, girls,",
    "start": 552.68,
    "duration": 2.296
  },
  {
    "text": "boys and men,",
    "start": 555.0,
    "duration": 1.456
  },
  {
    "text": "upon transition back into society.",
    "start": 556.48,
    "duration": 2.56
  },
  {
    "text": "I never thought",
    "start": 560.96,
    "duration": 1.6
  },
  {
    "text": "that one day",
    "start": 563.44,
    "duration": 1.736
  },
  {
    "text": "I would be giving stories",
    "start": 565.2,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "of the injustices that are so common",
    "start": 567.12,
    "duration": 3.536
  },
  {
    "text": "within the criminal justice system,",
    "start": 570.68,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "but here I am.",
    "start": 574.36,
    "duration": 1.44
  },
  {
    "text": "Every time I go back to prison,",
    "start": 577.48,
    "duration": 2.12
  },
  {
    "text": "I feel a little at home,",
    "start": 580.52,
    "duration": 1.92
  },
  {
    "text": "but it is the daunting work",
    "start": 583.24,
    "duration": 4.856
  },
  {
    "text": "to achieve the vision",
    "start": 588.12,
    "duration": 1.936
  },
  {
    "text": "that keeps me awake at night,",
    "start": 590.08,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "connecting the miles to Louisiana,",
    "start": 594.08,
    "duration": 4.016
  },
  {
    "text": "which is deemed as the incarceration\ncapital of the world,",
    "start": 598.12,
    "duration": 5.4
  },
  {
    "text": "carrying with me stories",
    "start": 604.24,
    "duration": 2.856
  },
  {
    "text": "of hundreds of women",
    "start": 607.12,
    "duration": 2.296
  },
  {
    "text": "whom I have met within the prisons,",
    "start": 609.44,
    "duration": 3.176
  },
  {
    "text": "some of whom are now\nembracing their second chances,",
    "start": 612.64,
    "duration": 4.536
  },
  {
    "text": "and others who are still\non that bridge of life's journey.",
    "start": 617.2,
    "duration": 5.24
  },
  {
    "text": "I embody a line",
    "start": 624.56,
    "duration": 1.72
  },
  {
    "text": "from the great Maya Angelou.",
    "start": 627.4,
    "duration": 2.48
  },
  {
    "text": "\"I come as one,",
    "start": 631.04,
    "duration": 2.536
  },
  {
    "text": "but I stand as 10,000.\"",
    "start": 633.6,
    "duration": 2.88
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 637.12,
    "duration": 4.08
  },
  {
    "text": "For my story is singular,",
    "start": 645.64,
    "duration": 3.456
  },
  {
    "text": "but imagine with me",
    "start": 649.12,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "the millions of people",
    "start": 651.68,
    "duration": 3.496
  },
  {
    "text": "in prisons today,",
    "start": 655.2,
    "duration": 2.24
  },
  {
    "text": "yearning for freedom.",
    "start": 658.28,
    "duration": 2.68
  },
  {
    "text": "Three years post my conviction",
    "start": 663.04,
    "duration": 4.176
  },
  {
    "text": "and two years post my release,",
    "start": 667.24,
    "duration": 3.416
  },
  {
    "text": "I got cleared by the courts of appeal",
    "start": 670.68,
    "duration": 2.976
  },
  {
    "text": "of any wrongdoing.",
    "start": 673.68,
    "duration": 1.536
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 675.24,
    "duration": 3.76
  },
  {
    "text": "Around the same time,",
    "start": 680.76,
    "duration": 2.056
  },
  {
    "text": "I got blessed with my son,",
    "start": 682.84,
    "duration": 2.176
  },
  {
    "text": "whom I named Uhuru,",
    "start": 685.04,
    "duration": 2.256
  },
  {
    "text": "which in my dialect means \"freedom.\"",
    "start": 687.32,
    "duration": 3.056
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 690.4,
    "duration": 4.056
  },
  {
    "text": "Because I had finally gotten the freedom",
    "start": 694.48,
    "duration": 3.496
  },
  {
    "text": "that I so longed for.",
    "start": 698.0,
    "duration": 1.88
  },
  {
    "text": "I come as one,",
    "start": 700.72,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "but I stand as 10,000,",
    "start": 702.88,
    "duration": 2.576
  },
  {
    "text": "encouraged by the hard-edged hope",
    "start": 705.48,
    "duration": 4.656
  },
  {
    "text": "that thousands of us have come together",
    "start": 710.16,
    "duration": 3.776
  },
  {
    "text": "to reform and transform\nthe criminal justice system,",
    "start": 713.96,
    "duration": 5.24
  },
  {
    "text": "encouraged that we are doing our jobs",
    "start": 720.0,
    "duration": 4.256
  },
  {
    "text": "as we are meant to do them.",
    "start": 724.28,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "And let us keep doing them",
    "start": 727.12,
    "duration": 2.376
  },
  {
    "text": "with no apology.",
    "start": 729.52,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you.",
    "start": 732.04,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 733.28,
    "duration": 3.52
  }
]